  "description": [
    "20 CITY CHILD LABOR LAWS CONDEMNED Agencies Council Told Acts i in Effect Here Fail to Give Protection The Washington Council of Social Agencies yesterday afternoon at a meeting in the Burlington Hotel adopted a resolution to refer the ques tion of child labor laws in the District to its childrens committee Mrs Whitman Cross chairman to see what can be done toward more rigidly en forcing such laws in the District The committee also wasauthorized to con rider other means of checking up on working minors The adoption of the resolution fol lowed an address by Miss Fay L lientley director of the department of attendance and work permits of the public schools in the District who charged that the local child labor laws nre not up to the standard set in various States and that there is no adequate provision for enforcing them What Washington should do regard Sng the governing of child labor greatly outweighs what it does she declared adding that little legal pro tection is afforded by the antiquated laws in operation Under the existing law requiring minors between the ages of 14 and 16 years of age to get special certificates to obtain regular"
